<br>
Dire Charm is reserved for 59+ so if you really want to make the axp comparison do:<br>
<br>
Lvl 48 to 60 + 27 axp points or<br>
<br>
1 mage epic quest*<br>
<br>
*most high end guilds have a necro parked on island 7 these days.  In a 4 hour weekday raid we grabbed 3 crowns so all the horrendous tales of this epic bit are far fetched.  Add the increase in earth staves and you suddenly have an epic quest within reach (albeit nothing compared to the rogue and monk)<br>
<br>
And don't even get me started on the Dire Charm vs. Epic Pet discussion.  Rombus and Tudamorf summoned it up quite clearly above.   It's like arguing that the wizard 17K crit mana blast is un balancing even though they could do twice that amount of damage chain casting bane damage spells.<br>
<br>
Apples and oranges really - I can't fathom why the mage community don't center their class balance discussion around something with more merit.<br>
